u = 4^{-x}
\int \frac{dx}{4^{-x} + 4^{x+1}}dx
\begin{align} \int \frac{dx}{4^{-x}+4^{x+1}} &= \int dx \frac{4^x}{1+4 \cdot 4^{2 x}} \\ &= \int dx \frac{e^{a x}}{1+4\, e^{2 a x}}\\ &= \frac1{4 a}\int \frac{dy}{\frac14+y^2} \\ &= \frac1{4 \log{2}} \arctan{(2 y)} +C \\ &= \frac1{4 \log{2}} \arctan{(2 \cdot 4^x)}+C\end{align}
a=\log{4} = 2 \log{2}
